{"word":"patior","priority":"★★☆","meanings":[{"part_of_speech":"verb","definition":"(ラテン語)苦しむ、耐える、経験する、許す","english_definition":"(Latin) to suffer, endure, experience, permit","examples":[{"sentence":"Deus non patitur malum.","translation":"神は悪を許さない。"}],"collocations":["pati dolorem (痛みを経験する)","pati famem (飢えに苦しむ)","pati frigus (寒さに苦しむ)","pati iniuriam (不正に苦しむ)","pati mortem (死を経験する)","pati naufragium (難破を経験する)"],"synonyms":["fero","sustineo","tolero","perfero","excipio","accipio"],"antonyms":["repello","vito","fugio"]}],"etymology":{"value":"印欧祖語の *peh₁- (打つ、傷つける)に由来すると考えられている。","priority":"★★★"},"pronunciation":{"ipa":"/ˈpatɪ.or/","syllables":"pa-ti-or"},"inflection":{"verb_forms":{"present_indicative":["patior","pateris","patitur","patimur","patimini","patiuntur"],"imperfect_indicative":["patiebar","patiebaris","patiebatur","patiebamur","patiebamini","patiebantur"],"future_indicative":["patiar","patieris","patietur","patiemur","patiemini","patientur"],"perfect_indicative":["passus sum","passus es","passus est","passi sumus","passi estis","passi sunt"],"pluperfect_indicative":["passus eram","passus eras","passus erat","passi eramus","passi eratis","passi erant"],"future_perfect_indicative":["passus ero","passus eris","passus erit","passi erimus","passi eritis","passi erunt"],"present_subjunctive":["patiar","patiaris","patiatur","patiamur","patiamini","patiantur"],"imperfect_subjunctive":["paterer","patereris","pateretur","pateremur","pateremini","paterentur"],"perfect_subjunctive":["passus sim","passus sis","passus sit","passi simus","passi sitis","passi sint"],"pluperfect_subjunctive":["passus essem","passus esses","passus esset","passi essemus","passi essetis","passi essent"],"present_infinitive":"pati","perfect_infinitive":"passum esse","future_infinitive":"passurum esse","present_participle":"patiens","future_participle":"passurus","gerund":"patiendi","gerundive":"patiendus"},"notes":"「patior」はdeponent動詞であり、能動態の形を持ちながら受動的な意味を持つ。"},"usage_notes":{"explanation":"「patior」は、苦しみ、困難、試練などを経験することを意味するラテン語の動詞です。物理的な苦痛だけでなく、精神的な苦しみや不利益、不正なども含みます。また、何かを許容する、容認するという意味合いもあります。派生語として、英語の「patience（忍耐）」、「passion（情熱）」、「passive（受動的な）」などがあります。","priority":"★★☆"},"common_mistakes":{"examples":[{"incorrect":"*patior facere","correct":"*sino facere","note":"「patior」は「許す」という意味で使われる場合、「sino」の方がより一般的です。"},{"incorrect":"*patior esse","correct":"*sum passus","note":"「苦しんでいる状態である」を表現する場合は、「sum passus」（完了分詞）を使用します。"}],"priority":"★☆☆"},"related_words":{"derivatives":["patientia (名詞: 忍耐)","passio (名詞: 苦しみ、情熱)","passivus (形容詞: 受動的な)","passibilis (形容詞: 苦しみやすい)","compassio (名詞: 同情)"],"english_derivatives":["patience","passion","passive","compassion"],"priority":"★★☆"},"level_frequency":{"notes":"古典ラテン語では頻繁に使用されるが、現代では学術的な文脈以外ではあまり使われない。","priority":"★☆☆"},"readability_explanation":{"level":"C1","text":"「patior」はラテン語の動詞で、「苦しむ」「耐える」「経験する」「許す」といった意味を持ちます。古典ラテン語の文献でよく見られ、哲学、文学、歴史などの分野で頻繁に登場します。英語の「patience」「passion」「passive」などの語源にもなっています。この単語を理解することで、ラテン語の文章の読解が深まり、関連する英語の語彙の理解も促進されます。"},"example_sentences":[{"sentence":"Milites pro patria multa passi sunt.","translation":"兵士たちは祖国のために多くの苦難を耐え忍んだ。","type":"example","meaning_category":"苦しむ、耐える"},{"sentence":"Patiens esto!","translation":"忍耐強くあれ！","type":"example","meaning_category":"苦しむ、耐える"},{"sentence":"Philosophus dicit se pati dolorem non timere.","translation":"哲学者は、自分は痛みに苦しむことを恐れていないと言う。","type":"example","meaning_category":"苦しむ、耐える"},{"sentence":"Non possum pati hanc iniuriam.","translation":"私はこの不正を許すことができない。","type":"example","meaning_category":"許す"},{"sentence":"Patior te abire.","translation":"私は君が行くのを許す。","type":"example","meaning_category":"許す"}]}